Well, I'm learning java now (let's see how long I have interest in it). Well, I started with some tuts yesterday, and this is the first thing I made by myself. It's a clock :P The format is better in my IDE, but the code blocks ruin it. Oh well, here it is :P

[code]
public class ripprogram{

	public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException  {

		int h = 0;
		int m = 0;
		int s = 0;

		while (s  < 61){
			System.out.println("Time: " + h + ":" + m + ":" +s);
			Thread.sleep(1000);
		s = s + 1;

		if (s == 60){
			m = m + 1;
			s = 0;

		if (m == 60){
			h = h + 1;
			m = 0;

		if (h == 25){
			h = 0;
		}
		}

		}
		}
	}
}
